  <h1>Form events & preventDefault</h1>

  <form action="#">
    <div id="inputDiv">
      <input type="text" />
      <button class="btn btn-outline-success">Submit</button>
    </div>
  </form>

  <p>
    When we have a form and the user submits it, the action we give the form
    element is where the form data will be returned to, or sent to by the
    user. Also, the website will change to that address by DEFAULT.
  </p>
  <img src="formHTML.png" alt="" />
  <p>If we wanted to stay on the same webpage, we would use preventDefault</p>
  <h2>preventDefault()</h2>
  <p>
    We start by creating an event listener to the form when it is submitted.
  </p>
  <img src="eventListenerFormCode.png" alt="" />
  <p>
    Now we can use preventDefault() to change the default behavior of the
    form, which is to change the website to the form action.
  </p>
  <p>
    To do this, we add preventDefault after the parameter name inside our
    function. This parameter is the auto-generated event object which we can
    name in any way when creating the function.
  </p>
  <img src="preventDefaultFormCode.png" alt="" />
  <p>Now, we will stay on the website even after submitting.</p>
  <h2>Example</h2>
  <p>
    Here we have an input for internet surfers, they can leave a comment by
    submitting the form.
  </p>
  <p>
    The comment will appear on the website, we will retrieve the form data and
    post it directly on the same page, without even having to refresh.
  </p>
  <img src="exampleCommentFormHTML.png" alt="" />
  <img src="exampleCommentFormJS.png" alt="" />
